{
  "texts": [
    "Lastly, they fed the acquired graph embedding vector and the feature vector of the source tweet into a fully connected layer for classification purposes.",
    "Thota et al. (2023) proposed a propagation-based method for early detection of rumors by capturing influential features and learning dynamic structures of their propagation.",
    "Their model consists of four modules: feature extraction, pattern matching, structure reconstruction, and rumor detection.",
    "Within the propagation graph, individual users are depicted as nodes, and node representations are generated using a 2-layer GCN.",
    "The edges within the graph are fed into the pattern matching algorithm, which recursively analyzes the data stream and generates a list of matched patterns along with their corresponding occurrence times."
  ]
}